    <description><![CDATA[LAV Filters are a set of DirectShow filters based on the libavformat and libavcodec libraries from the ffmpeg project, which will allow you to play virtually any format in a DirectShow player.
]]></description>
    <summary>Open-Source DirectShow Media Splitter and Decoders</summary>
    <releaseNotes><![CDATA[[Releases](https://github.com/Nevcairiel/LAVFilters/releases)

**0.81.0 - 2026/01/12**
**LAV Splitter**
- NEW: Support for APV (Advanced Professional Video) video streams
- Fixed: VVC in MP4 without CTTS did not play properly
- Fixed: AV1 streams with invalid metadata did not get handled correctly

**LAV Video**
- NEW: Support for decoding APV (Advanced Professional Video)
- Changed: Re-designed pixel format mapping to be based on a heuristic rather then hard-coded, improving support for rarely-used formats
- Fixed: Deinterlacing of 4:2:2 videos was broken in 0.80

**LAV Audio**
- Fixed: Bitstreaming TrueHD from Blu-rays with seamless branching could result in out-of-sync audio, or a noticeable gap]]></releaseNotes>
